. Step 1: Jenkins Introduction :::::::

-> Jenkins ek open-source CI/CD tool hai.
-> Use hota hai code build, test, deploy automatically karne ke liye.
-> Written in Java.
-> Website: https://www.jenkins.io

. Step 2: Jenkins Installation ::::::::

  1 -> Server Setup: Ubuntu 22.04 (AMI)
  2 -> Install Jenkins + Git + Java (JDK) + Maven:

      sudo apt update        -----> for update
      sudo apt install openjdk-17-jdk -----> for java
      sudo apt install git maven-------> for Maven
      wget -q -O - https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian/jenkins.io.key | sudo apt-key add -                             _------------> For Jenkins link
      sudo sh -c 'echo deb https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian binary/ > /etc/apt/sources.list.d/jenkins.list'         ------------->
      sudo apt update    
      sudo apt install jenkins --> install jenkins



